Strengthens our thesis Impact to our thesis
Meaningful shortfall Financial results versus consensus
Modest revision lower Direction of next 12- month consensus EPS
Source: Company data, Morgan Stanley Research
The shortfall vs. our estimate was mainly on cost overruns due to sorting centre relocations. Management does not expect such impact in 2H25.
Yunda did not follow peers' aggressive pricing strategies since Apr- 25, leading to a 0.7ppt market share loss for the quarter.
The company expects industry ASP to improve in 2H25 vs. 2Q25. Peak season could help support pricing.

Yunda reported 1H25 recurring net profit of Rmb453mn, down 46% YoY. Implied 2Q25 recurring profit was Rmb144mn, down 68% YoY, well below our estimate. Yunda attributed the recurring earnings miss mainly to Rmb180mn in one- off costs for sorting centers relocation. Excluding that, 2Q25 recurring profit fell 21% YoY, largely in line with MSe amid competition, we estimate.

Implied recurring unit profit for the quarter was Rmb0.02, vs. Rmb0.05 in 1Q25 and Rmb0.07 in 2Q24. That is lower than the Rmb0.03 unit profit for STO in 2Q25. Volume grew 11% YoY in 2Q25. ASP fell 5% YoY in 2Q25, vs. declines of 5- 6% for ZTO and YTO. Unit costs declined 2% YoY in 2Q25. OCF in 1H25 dropped 50% YoY to Rmb1.0bn, vs. capex of Rmb1.1bn and lease payments of Rmb153mn, indicating negative free cash flow.
MORGAN STANLEY ASIA LIMITED+
Carlos Liu, CFA Research Associate
Hong Kong/China Transportation & Infrastructure | China
